data.title: Princess Marie of Prussia and Princess Louise Margaret, Duchess of Connaught
data.meta_description: Cabinet photograph of Princess Marie of Prussia (1855-88) (left), and her sister Princess Louise Margaret of Connaught (1860-1917) (right), standing outside by a double door, and a rug on the steps. This may be at Bagshot Park, the newly-rebuilt house acquired by the Duke of Connaught. Princess Marie of Prussia was first married to Prince Hendrik of the Netherlands but he died of measles six months later.
